Class DescribeFlowLogsRequest

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.amazonaws.AmazonWebServiceRequest
      • com.amazonaws.services.ec2.model.DescribeFlowLogsRequest
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable

    public class DescribeFlowLogsRequest
extends AmazonWebServiceRequest
implements java.io.Serializable
    Container for the parameters to the DescribeFlowLogs operation.

    Describes one or more flow logs. To view the information in your flow logs (the log streams for the network interfaces), you must use the CloudWatch Logs console or the CloudWatch Logs API.

    See Also:
    AmazonEC2.describeFlowLogs(DescribeFlowLogsRequest), Serialized Form
